<section class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="faq-group accordion">
      <h3>Before your tan</h3>
      <details><summary>How should I prepare for my spray tan?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Exfoliate 24 hours before, shave or wax at least 12 hours before, and skip lotions, deodorants, and perfumes the day of your appointment.</div></details>
      <details><summary>What should I wear to my appointment?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Wear loose, dark clothing. Avoid tight bras, leggings, or jeans for at least 8 hours after your tan.</div></details>

      <h3>During your appointment</h3>
      <details><summary>How long does a spray tan take?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Most custom tans take 15–20 minutes from start to finish.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Is the spray tan solution safe?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Yes. Our solutions are made with natural ingredients, including eCO-certified dihydroxyacetone (DHA). They're cruelty-free, paraben-free, and alcohol-free.</div></details>

      <h3>Aftercare</h3>
      <details><summary>How long until I can shower?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Wait at least 8 hours for a rapid tan or per your specialist's guidance for other tans before your first rinse.</div></details>
      <details><summary>When can I get wet?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Avoid water, sweating, and tight clothing during the development window. After your first rinse, your tan is set.</div></details>
      <details><summary>How long does the tan last?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Typically 7–10 days with proper aftercare. Use our Tan Extender to maintain your glow longer.</div></details>

      <h3>Memberships & packages</h3>
      <details><summary>Can I freeze my membership?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Yes — contact your studio directly for membership pauses.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Do packages expire?</summary><div class="rte text-muted">Packages are valid for one year from purchase.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
